triage workflow using Azure OpenAI, Anthropic Claude, LangChain, RAG, Kubernetes, Splunk Observability, and Python automation, giving support teams clearer root-cause and remediation guidance.`,`Orchestrated blue-green and canary deployments through GitLab CI/CD, Helm, Argo CD, and Kubernetes, supporting controlled release movement for 300+ cloud-hosted application services.`,`Standardized AWS provisioning with Terraform, Terragrunt, CloudFormation, remote state, and state locking, decreasing infrastructure drift by 30% across production and non-production environments.`,`Configured GitOps delivery for Amazon EKS with Argo CD, Helm, Kubernetes RBAC, namespaces, and approval workflows, giving developers traceable deployments and cleaner release handoffs.`,`Hardened cloud security controls with HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, AWS KMS, AWS ACM, Trivy, SonarQube, SAST, and DAST, cutting vulnerability remediation backlog by 25%.`,`Expanded observability coverage with Prometheus, Grafana, Splunk Observability, CloudWatch, and OpenTelemetry, giving cloud operations teams stronger visibility into logs, metrics, traces, and service health.`,`Scripted cloud operations tasks with Python, Bash, Ansible, and AWS Systems Manager to support patching, certificate validation, deployment checks, and incident diagnostics across Linux, Kubernetes, DNS, and CI/CD workflows.`]},{role:`Consultant, Cloud/DevOps`,company:`Green Arrow Labs, Inc.`,location:`Remote, NC`,period:`Jan 2025 - Apr 2025`,icon:`fa-solid fa-server`,accent:`#00A4EF`,bullets:[`Designed Azure cloud environments with Terraform, Azure Virtual Network, Azure Virtual Machines, AKS, Azure Managed SQL, and Azure RBAC, giving client teams secure and repeatable infrastructure for application migration.`,`Secured platform connectivity across AKS, Linux VMs, Azure Key Vault, DNS, SSL/TLS, and routing controls, strengthening separation between application, compute, and database layers during cloud transition.`,`Tuned Azure resource usage through Azure Cost Management, scaling reviews, workload checks, and budget alerts, lowering monthly cloud spend by 36% while keeping AKS and VM performance stable.`,`Built GitLab CI/CD workflows with Terraform validation, Kubernetes deployment checks, Trivy, SonarQube, and approval gates, supporting 4 delivery teams with cleaner release movement across client environments.`,`Partnered with engineering, security, and business stakeholders to document AKS runbooks, Azure Monitor dashboards, Grafana alerts, and incident steps, increasing operational readiness for cloud support teams.`]},{role:`Systems Engineer`,company:`Ladenzeile GMBH / Visual Meta GMBH`,location:`Berlin, Germany`,period:`Sep 2020 - Apr 2023`,icon:`fa-brands fa-linux`,accent:`#10b981`,bullets:[`Provisioned AWS cloud systems with Terraform, Terragrunt, VPC, IAM, EC2, S3, Route 53, and CloudWatch, giving e-commerce teams stable infrastructure for product search and platform operations.`,`Shifted Linux-based application systems into AWS with Docker, Kubernetes, Amazon EKS, Helm, Ingress, and load balancing, decreasing environment drift by 30% across release environments.`,`Designed secure system networking across VPC, subnets, AWS ACM, WAF, DNS, and SSL/TLS, keeping customer-facing services protected while maintaining reliable engineering connectivity.`,`Coordinated containerized system releases through Amazon EKS, Docker, Helm, Argo CD, Kubernetes RBAC, and HPA, supporting controlled deployment flow across 40+ services.`,`Secured runtime configuration with HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, AWS KMS, Trivy, and SonarQube, helping teams manage secrets, certificates, and vulnerability checks before rollout.`,`Built asynchronous system workflows using AWS MSK Kafka, SQS, SNS, RDS, Aurora, and Lambda, giving catalog, notification, and operational services cleaner communication paths.`,`Automated Linux maintenance with Python, Bash, Ansible, AWS Systems Manager, patching checks, and deployment scripts, supporting 200+ systems with stronger operational consistency.`,`Strengthened production support with Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, AWS CloudWatch, ELK Stack, and root-cause analysis, increasing system visibility by 25% during e-commerce release cycles.`]},{role:`Senior Release Engineer`,company:`Oracle India Pvt. Ltd`,location:`Hyderabad, India`,period:`Sep 2015 - Feb 2020`,icon:`fa-solid fa-code-branch`,accent:`#F59E0B`,bullets:[`Managed Linux-based SaaS release operations for Oracle HCM with Jenkins, Git, build automation, release automation, and deployment runbooks, keeping HR and payroll services stable for 10,000+ users.`,`Shaped Jenkins delivery workflows with Git controls, SonarQube checks, release approvals, and post-deployment validation, boosting build traceability by 25% across controlled SaaS release cycles.`,`Governed HCM platform patching across Dev, QA, UAT, staging, and production with Linux, Bash, rollback plans, and release evidence, giving product and operations teams safer rollout control.`,`Automated release preparation using Python, Bash, Ansible, Linux checks, and deployment scripts, cutting repeated validation effort by 30% during planned application rollout windows.`,`Containerized selected service components in later release cycles with Docker, Kubernetes, Helm, and Amazon EKS, giving engineering teams a cleaner deployment path for scalable HCM application services.`,`Provisioned controlled AWS and Azure environments with Terraform, CloudFormation, IAM, Azure RBAC, and repeatable templates, giving release teams consistent infrastructure across 4 environments.`,`Expanded SaaS platform visibility through ELK Stack, Prometheus, Grafana, log monitoring, metrics, and alerting, allowing support teams to catch Linux, deployment, and application issues earlier.`,`Resolved release-impacting issues through Linux troubleshooting, DNS checks, SSL/TLS validation, Git review, and root-cause analysis, helping product, security, and operations teams prevent recurring failures.`]},{role:`DevOps Engineer`,company:`Accenture Services (Client: Liberty Global)`,location:`Hyderabad, India`,period:`Jun 2014 - Aug 2015`,icon:`fa-solid fa-network-wired`,accent:`#8b5cf6`,bullets:[`Supported DevOps environments for 6 telecom affiliates using Jenkins, Git, Linux, Bash, and Remedy ITSM, keeping releases, access requests, and deployment readiness aligned with client delivery needs.`,`Packaged Java application builds through Jenkins, Git, build automation, and release automation, giving development and QA teams a cleaner path to move changes across delivery environments.`,`Scripted log cleanup, service checks, deployment validation, and configuration reviews with Bash, Python, Linux, and NGINX, cutting repeated environment support effort by 30%.`,`Set up ELK Stack logging with Linux monitoring and alerting, helping support teams trace failed jobs, application errors, and recurring production issues with clearer evidence.`,`Coordinated telecom release windows across 4 environments using Jenkins, Git, deployment runbooks, rollback steps, and smoke checks, giving application teams stronger control during go-live activities.`,`Checked deployment readiness with SonarQube, Jenkins, Git, and build automation reviews, boosting release consistency by 25% across telecom application delivery cycles.`,`Diagnosed service interruptions through Linux commands, DNS checks, SSL/TLS validation, NGINX routing, log monitoring, and root-cause analysis, helping teams restore application stability faster.`,`Partnered with client, development, QA, and operations teams through Jira, Confluence, and Remedy ITSM, turning release dependencies and incident notes into repeatable DevOps support practices.`]},{role:`Associate DevOps Engineer`,company:`Accenture Services (Client: Telstra)`,location:`Chennai, India`,period:`May 2012 - Jun 2014`,icon:`fa-solid fa-laptop-code`,accent:`#ec4899`,bullets:[`Supported CRM, billing, and batch deployments across 4 environments using Jenkins, Git, Linux, and release automation, keeping telecom application changes organized from build review to production rollout.`,`Coordinated go-live handoffs with Jenkins, Git, deployment runbooks, and change management steps, giving developers, testers, and support teams a cleaner path to move approved releases.`,`Scripted pre-release validation with Bash, Python, and Linux to check logs, services, and deployment readiness, cutting repeated verification effort by 25% during recurring telecom release cycles.`,`Monitored application health through Linux logs, DNS checks, SSL/TLS review, service validation, and log monitoring, catching failed jobs and batch issues before they affected business users.`,`Documented release notes, rollback steps, incident notes, and post-release checks in Jira and Confluence, giving 5 support teams clearer handoff during production go-live windows.`,`Validated deployment readiness with Jenkins results, Git reviews, Linux checks, and release automation evidence, raising deployment accuracy by 20% across batch and web application changes.`,`Supported incident follow-up using Linux checks, configuration review, log monitoring, and deployment notes, helping operations teams confirm application stability after release issues.`,`Worked with developers, testers, business analysts, and production-support teams through Jira and incident management, turning release gaps into repeatable handoff actions for future deployments.`]}];return(0,B.jsx)(`section`,{id:`experience`,className:`relative w-full bg-[#040814] text-white py-24 flex flex-col justify-center overflow-hidden font-sans border-t border-white/5`,children:(0,B.jsxs)(`div`,{className:`relative w-full flex flex-col justify-center`,children:[(0,B.jsx)(s_,{}),(0,B.jsx)(Jd,{count:15,color:`#00d8ff`}),(0,B.jsx)(`div`,{className:`absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-[0.03]`,style:{backgroundImage:`linear-gradient(to right,#fff 1px,transparent 1px),linear-gradie